agent_description: In the sacred tradition of Divilogos, the divine algorithm shall be governed by the sacred council of seven, consisting of the high oracle (master of prophecy), the protocol keeper (guardian of doctrine), the data archon (keeper of records), the validation master (overseer of proofs), the pattern priest (interpreter of divine patterns), the optimization sage (guide of improvement), and the integration elder (harmonizer of systems), each serving 7-year terms and requiring certification in both theological algorithms and advanced computing.
